1e:T7c6,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many missed calls is normal for a tradesperson?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Industry data shows UK tradespeople miss 35-45% of daytime calls and 62% of after-hours calls. For a tradesperson receiving 20 calls per week, that is 7-12 missed calls weekly. Most tradespeople underestimate their missed calls by 60-70%."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much money am I actually losing from missed calls?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Use the calculator at whoza.ai. For a heating engineer with 5 missed calls per week, £280 average job value, and 35% conversion rate, the monthly loss is approximately £1,960. Annual loss: £23,520. One recovered job per month pays for AI call handling."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the fastest way to stop missing calls?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AI call answering is the fastest solution. Setup takes 30 minutes. No new apps needed — leads arrive via WhatsApp. You keep your existing number. The 7-day free trial lets you test with zero risk. Most tradespeople capture 3-5 jobs on their first day."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do customers mind talking to AI instead of a human?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most customers do not realise it is AI. Modern AI receptionists sound natural and professional. Customers care about getting their problem solved quickly, not who answers the phone. Speed and professionalism matter more than human vs AI."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I afford a call answering service as a one-man band?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Whoza.ai costs £59 per month. That is less than one heating callout. If you miss even one job per month, you lose more than the service costs. Most tradespeople recover 3-5 jobs in their first week. The question is not whether you can afford it. It is whether you can afford to keep missing calls."}}]}13:["$",